PROJECT: Old Money Web Application
FORMAT: Minimalistic Technical Specification (Design + Style)
TARGET DEVICES:
- Desktop (standard widths)
- Tablets (priority: iPad Pro)
- Mobile (priority: iPhone 17 Max + common iPhone sizes)

---------------------------------------------------------
1. NAVIGATION BUTTONS
---------------------------------------------------------
- Style: compact, minimal, icon-first.
- Shape: rounded-rectangle or pill, 4–6px radius.
- Padding: minimal (6–8px horizontal, 4–6px vertical).
- Alignment: right-aligned in header, tightly grouped.
- Buttons required:
  - Refresh
  - Close
- Hover/active states: subtle color shift only (no animation).

---------------------------------------------------------
2. TEXT FONTS
---------------------------------------------------------
- Primary font: classic serif or refined sans-serif.
  Recommended families:
  - Serif: "Georgia", "Playfair Display", "Cormorant"
  - Sans-serif: "Inter", "Helvetica Neue", "SF Pro"
- Font weights:
  - Header title: medium or semibold
  - Navigation buttons: regular
  - Body text: regular
- Font sizes (responsive):
  - Desktop: 16–18px base
  - Tablet: 17–19px base
  - Mobile: 15–17px base

---------------------------------------------------------
3. COLOR SYSTEM
---------------------------------------------------------
- Overall aesthetic: “old money” — understated, neutral, elegant.
- Background colors:
  - Primary background: off‑white (#F7F7F2) or warm ivory (#FAF8F2)
  - Header/footer background: muted olive-gray (#D7D5C9) or soft taupe (#CFC9BD)
- Text colors:
  - Primary text: deep charcoal (#2A2A2A)
  - Secondary text: muted gray (#6A6A6A)
- Button colors:
  - Default: soft neutral (#E0DED6)
  - Hover: slightly darker (#C9C7BF)
  - Active: darker neutral (#B5B3AC)
- Borders:
  - Thin, subtle (#C8C8C8)

---------------------------------------------------------
4. HEADER STYLE
---------------------------------------------------------
- Fixed top position.
- Height: compact (48–56px depending on device).
- Layout:
  - Left: Title “Old Money”
  - Right: Navigation button group (Refresh, Close)
- Spacing: minimal margins, tight alignment.
- Typography: serif or refined sans-serif, semibold.
- Background: muted neutral (see color system).
- No shadows; optional 1px bottom border.

---------------------------------------------------------
5. FOOTER STYLE
---------------------------------------------------------
- Minimal height (32–40px).
- Content:
  - Copyright: “CoolPortals”
  - Timestamp: auto-generated
- Alignment: centered or right-aligned depending on layout.
- Background: same palette as header or slightly lighter.
- No shadows; thin top border.

---------------------------------------------------------
6. BODY LAYOUT
---------------------------------------------------------
- Description text: “Hello world”.
- Metadata block:
  - File name (dynamic)
  - Copyright
  - Timestamp
- Captions:
  - Always placed directly above input fields.
  - Minimal spacing (2–4px).
- Input fields:
  - Compact height (28–32px mobile, 32–36px desktop).
  - Full-width on mobile.
  - Moderate width on desktop/tablet.
  - Minimal borders, no shadows.

---------------------------------------------------------
7. RESPONSIVE RULES
---------------------------------------------------------
Desktop:
- Header fixed, full width.
- Navigation buttons right-aligned.
- Content centered with minimal margins.

Tablet (iPad Pro):
- Slightly increased font size.
- Touch-friendly button spacing (but still compact).
- Maintain minimalistic layout.

Mobile (iPhone 17 Max + others):
- Header collapses to single row.
- Buttons become icon-only.
- Inputs full-width.
- Typography slightly smaller.
- Tight vertical spacing.

---------------------------------------------------------
8. IMPROVEMENTS ADDED
---------------------------------------------------------
- Unified color palette aligned with “old money” aesthetic.
- Consistent typography system.
- Clear spacing rules for captions and inputs.
- Defined header/footer border logic.
- Responsive font scaling.
- Icon-first navigation for mobile.
- Compact button geometry for all devices.

---------------------------------------------------------
9. QUESTIONS FOR YOU (NEEDED TO FINALIZE)
---------------------------------------------------------
1. Should the navigation buttons use icons only, text only, or icon + text on desktop?
2. Do you want dark mode support?
3. Should the footer always be visible (fixed) or scroll with content?
4. Do you prefer serif or sans-serif as the primary font?
5. Should the app use a grid system (e.g., 12-column) or free-form layout?

---------------------------------------------------------
END OF SPECIFICATION
---------------------------------------------------------

